Effective cost optimization helps organizations maximize cloud value without sacrificing performance.

Best practices include:

* Right-size virtual machines
* Shut down unused resources
* Use Reserved Instances for predictable workloads
* Adopt Auto Scaling
* Apply resource tags for cost tracking
* Monitor spending with Azure Cost Management

For example, a development team automatically shuts down non-production VMs outside office hours.

A real-life use case is startups controlling operational expenses while scaling.

Another example is enterprises identifying idle resources to reduce unnecessary costs.

Cost optimization is an ongoing operational responsibility.
